    <node id="LOGGING">
      <data key="d0">LOGGING</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">LOGGING is a database feature enabled on multiple tables, including HR.JOB_HISTORY, HR.EMPLOYEES, LOCATIONS, and DEPARTMENTS. This feature records changes made to these tables to support recovery and auditing purposes, ensuring that modifications are tracked and can be reviewed or restored if necessary.&lt;SEP&gt;LOGGING is a database feature enabled on the HR.COUNTRIES table that records changes to the table for recovery and auditing purposes.</data>
