    <node id="LOCATIONS Table">
      <data key="d0">LOCATIONS Table</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">LOCATIONS Table is a presumed related database table that stores location data, which LOCATION_ID in hr.DEPARTMENTS likely references as a foreign key.&lt;SEP&gt;The LOCATIONS table contains data about physical locations, referenced by the DEPARTMENTS table to indicate where departments are situated.&lt;SEP&gt;The LOCATIONS table is a database table within the hr schema that stores detailed information about physical locations related to the company, including offices, warehouses, and production sites. It supports business processes such as logistics, human resources, supply chain management, and regional reporting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-852dbb615191c11928edcccd02fc0463&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1164983175b10bbf01dc0af45ebb0360&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cc87664b23138933a8c4a307851a3c6</data>
