    <node id="LOCATION_ID">
      <data key="d0">LOCATION_ID</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">LOCATION_ID is a column in the hr.DEPARTMENTS table representing location identifiers, likely referencing a locations table, used for filtering, sorting, and joining department data based on location.&lt;SEP&gt;LOCATION_ID is a column in the hr.DEPARTMENTS table used as the key for the Hr.DEPT_LOCATION_IX index to organize data by location.&lt;SEP&gt;LOCATION_ID is a numeric field that serves as a key identifier in the HR database schema. In the HR.LOCATIONS table, LOCATION_ID is the primary key column, uniquely identifying each location record with a non-null numeric identifier (NUMBER(4)), which supports fast lookups and ensures data integrity. In the HR.DEPARTMENTS table, LOCATION_ID functions as a foreign key column that references the LOCATION_ID in the LOCATIONS table, indicating the physical location of each department. This foreign key is nullable to accommodate departments that may not have an assigned location, thereby supporting accurate location-based data and reporting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f863663ead003b009e2b4af32de47158&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1164983175b10bbf01dc0af45ebb0360&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e9ada454ac1183005c56f36d696a2bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cc87664b23138933a8c4a307851a3c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-852dbb615191c11928edcccd02fc0463&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6a1efa3aade4dbc0431fee65f96b499</data>
