    <node id="COUNTRY_ID">
      <data key="d0">COUNTRY_ID</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">COUNTRY_ID is a fixed-length two-character primary key identifier for countries in the HR.COUNTRIES table, ensuring uniqueness and fast lookup.&lt;SEP&gt;COUNTRY_ID is a fixed-length, 2-character CHAR column in the HR.LOCATIONS table that serves as a foreign key referencing the COUNTRIES table. This design ensures referential integrity between location and country data while optimizing storage and indexing for country codes. The COUNTRY_ID column is used for filtering and joining location data by country and is nullable.&lt;SEP&gt;COUNTRY_ID is a primary key column in the HR.COUNTRIES table that uniquely identifies each country record. Updates to this column are restricted due to primary key constraints.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f863663ead003b009e2b4af32de47158&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32be534f99a9a53fb69794f282e09f45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f9fdf4c76d1900d14f7ab7687630396&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7bffbbc9cb2999db53c7a202e9b176d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1164983175b10bbf01dc0af45ebb0360&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-799db255698d9ddf0d4c7649135906d0</data>
