    <node id="COUNTRIES Table">
      <data key="d0">COUNTRIES Table</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The COUNTRIES table contains country data and is linked to the HR.LOCATIONS table to provide country names and details, supporting geographic reporting and analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;The COUNTRIES table is a related database table referenced by the LOCATIONS table via the COUNTRY_ID foreign key, storing valid country codes and related country information.&lt;SEP&gt;The COUNTRIES table is a referenced entity likely containing country data, which COUNTRY_ID in hr.LOCATIONS references as a foreign key.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f863663ead003b009e2b4af32de47158&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1164983175b10bbf01dc0af45ebb0360&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f9fdf4c76d1900d14f7ab7687630396</data>
