    <node id="hr Schema">
      <data key="d0">hr Schema</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The hr schema is a database schema that organizes human resources-related data and contains several tables and associated objects. It includes the LOCATIONS table, which is indexed by both the LOC_COUNTRY_IX and LOC_CITY_IX indexes. Additionally, the schema contains the COUNTRIES and DEPARTMENTS tables, with the DEPARTMENTS table being supported by the DEPT_LOCATION_IX index. Overall, the hr schema encompasses multiple tables and indexes designed to manage and structure human resources data effectively.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1164983175b10bbf01dc0af45ebb0360&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cc87664b23138933a8c4a307851a3c6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70313252212b24335f3373f61fa80d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f9fdf4c76d1900d14f7ab7687630396</data>
