    <node id="Logging">
      <data key="d0">Logging</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Logging in databases refers to the process of recording operations and changes, which can impact performance and recovery. Specifically, logging is enabled on several tables within the HR schema, including HR.REGIONS, HR.LOCATIONS, and HR.JOBS. On the HR.REGIONS table, logging records changes to support recovery and auditing, ensuring data durability and traceability. Similarly, logging on the HR.LOCATIONS table captures changes in redo logs to facilitate data recovery and auditing. The HR.JOBS table also has logging enabled to record all data manipulation language (DML) operations, further supporting recovery and auditing processes. Overall, logging across these tables ensures that changes are systematically recorded to maintain data integrity, support recovery efforts, and provide audit trails.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-af654ef872447926942a03d22d7c2936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f863663ead003b009e2b4af32de47158&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f36c7f7c4e6a172a92fe1ea27e35db14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-799db255698d9ddf0d4c7649135906d0</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753913673</data>
    </node>
