    <node id="LOC_CITY_IX">
      <data key="d0">LOC_CITY_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">LOC_CITY_IX is a non-unique B-tree index on the CITY column of the hr.LOCATIONS table, designed to optimize query performance for city-based lookups and sorting. It uses NOLOGGING to reduce redo log generation during creation or maintenance, has no compression, and does not support parallel operations. It supports efficient geographic data retrieval in business processes involving location information.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b70313252212b24335f3373f61fa80d1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753912721</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LOCATIONS">
      <data key="d0">LOCATIONS</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">LOCATIONS is a database table in the hr schema that stores geographic or address-related data for business entities such as offices, warehouses, or stores.&lt;SEP&gt;LOCATIONS is a database table in the hr schema that stores geographic or office location data, including a CITY column used for filtering and reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;LOCATIONS is an organizational entity referenced by the HR.DEPARTMENTS table to obtain physical location information for departments.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1e9ada454ac1183005c56f36d696a2bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70313252212b24335f3373f61fa80d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38310d95744bbc5c98b7150c7d4a14b6</data>
