    </node>
    <node id="Index Maintenance">
      <data key="d0">Index Maintenance</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Index Maintenance encompasses a range of activities focused on monitoring, analyzing, and rebuilding database indexes to address fragmentation and prevent performance degradation. This process involves regular health checks of indexes such as HR.EMP_NAME_IX, HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX, JHIST_JOB_IX, the primary key index on the HR.REGIONS table, and LOC_CITY_IX. The maintenance tasks ensure optimal query performance and sustained database efficiency, particularly following bulk data changes. Additionally, Index Maintenance includes considerations for options like NOLOGGING and NOPARALLEL to optimize logging behavior and parallelism during rebuilds, as well as recovery planning to enhance reliability. Overall, these comprehensive efforts maintain the integrity and performance of database indexes.&lt;SEP&gt;Index Maintenance refers to the operations involved in creating, rebuilding, or maintaining the HR.JHIST_EMPLOYEE_IX index, affected by options like NOLOGGING and NOPARALLEL.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d7c88e676a8afc774890f3b5fe6b5e9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f9fdf4c76d1900d14f7ab7687630396&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f86e46cc1908ec692fd894457e73ecd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70ec50d5fc775abc7249f3133791bd96&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-711d8bcdc23c815a60cb46edd6c7c69e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70313252212b24335f3373f61fa80d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c484da9a0a9ad0591728777ccd6d9bb8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-654140961a0c915ed4f93c4eca2a34d6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753913728</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Storage and Logging Options">
      <data key="d0">Storage and Logging Options</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Storage and Logging Options encompass the NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL settings applied to the HR.EMP_MANAGER_IX index to optimize performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Storage and logging options refer to the settings applied to LOC_CITY_IX, including NOLOGGING, NOCOMPRESS, and NOPARALLEL, which affect performance, storage size, and recovery.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f86e46cc1908ec692fd894457e73ecd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70313252212b24335f3373f61fa80d1</data>
