    <node id="REGION_ID">
      <data key="d0">REGION_ID</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">REGION_ID is a foreign key column in the HR.COUNTRIES table that links each country to a geographic region defined in the HR.REGIONS table.&lt;SEP&gt;REGION_ID is a numeric foreign key in HR.COUNTRIES referencing HR.REGIONS.REGION_ID, associating each country with a region for hierarchical geographic grouping and analysis.&lt;SEP&gt;REGION_ID is the primary key column of the HR.REGIONS table, a unique numeric identifier for each geographic region, ensuring data integrity and fast access.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-32be534f99a9a53fb69794f282e09f45&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7bffbbc9cb2999db53c7a202e9b176d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f36c7f7c4e6a172a92fe1ea27e35db14</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
