      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The Regions table is a base table within the HR schema that contains regional geographic data associated with countries and locations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Regions table within the HR schema stores regional information including region name.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9065b661548e2fda446d88c1a5d4a9b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc669b8fd76a2bbd4d405cb958121319</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753912987</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Employee">
      <data key="d0">Employee</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">An employee is an individual working within an organization, characterized by attributes such as employee ID, job role, manager, department, salary, and commission percentage.&lt;SEP&gt;Employee refers to an individual who works for an organization and whose job-related data is managed within HR systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-de63f99d53b08ae50d0a514c85b6afd2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9065b661548e2fda446d88c1a5d4a9b7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753913041</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Manager">
      <data key="d0">Manager</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A manager is an employee who supervises other employees, represented by the manager_id referencing employee_id within the Employees table, establishing a hierarchical relationship.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9065b661548e2fda446d88c1a5d4a9b7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
