    <node id="HR.EMP_NAME_IX">
      <data key="d0">HR.EMP_NAME_IX</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">HR.EMP_NAME_IX is a non-unique, ascending B-tree index on the LAST_NAME and FIRST_NAME columns of the HR.EMPLOYEES table, designed to optimize queries involving employee name lookups and sorting in a human resources context. It uses NOLOGGING to reduce redo log generation, disables compression to avoid CPU overhead, and disallows parallel operations, balancing performance and resource management.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d7c88e676a8afc774890f3b5fe6b5e9b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753913361</data>
    </node>
    <node id="LAST_NAME Column">
      <data key="d0">LAST_NAME Column</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">LAST_NAME is a column in the HR.EMPLOYEES table, typically defined as a VARCHAR2 or similar string type, storing employees' last names. It is indexed in ascending order by HR.EMP_NAME_IX to optimize name-based queries.&lt;SEP&gt;The LAST_NAME column in the HR.EMPLOYEES table stores employees' last names and is part of the B-tree index key.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d7c88e676a8afc774890f3b5fe6b5e9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f3a649840d8c0d19c4f0b28731832a5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1753913361</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FIRST_NAME Column">
      <data key="d0">FIRST_NAME Column</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">FIRST_NAME is a column in the HR.EMPLOYEES table, typically defined as a VARCHAR2 or similar string type, storing employees' first names. It is indexed in ascending order by HR.EMP_NAME_IX to optimize name-based queries.&lt;SEP&gt;The FIRST_NAME column in the HR.EMPLOYEES table stores employees' first names and is part of the B-tree index key.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d7c88e676a8afc774890f3b5fe6b5e9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f3a649840d8c0d19c4f0b28731832a5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
