      <data key="d0">HR.JOBS Table</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The HR.JOBS table is a foundational human resources reference table that defines all job roles within an organization. It enforces uniqueness and mandatory naming of jobs, supports optional salary range definitions, and integrates tightly with employee and payroll systems. It is designed for data integrity, auditability, and efficient access, making it a critical component of the HR database schema.</data>
